RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAIL COLUMBIA dueled inside of CLASSY AND FAST for the lead in opening stages then shook free mid-way around the turn, saved ground entering the lane, drew off under a drive then finished ridden out in late stages. JERI DAWN was reserved racing in the back, saved ground around the turn, tipped wider for the drive and cleared second best. CHEER UP tracked the top pair two wide into the turn, hustled up three wide into the lane and produced a mild bid for a share. CLASSY AND FAST dueled for the lead in opening stages, could not move on with the eventual winner past the midway point around the turn, continued to chase after rival into upper stretch then gave way. GOLD MAKER took a solid bump at the start but recovered quickly and raced just off the top pair, tracked rivals around the turn, came under a ride heading into the lane and had no response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UXMAL sped to the lead at the start and drifted three paths wide entering the first turn, set the pace along the inside up the backstretch, turned back the bid from UNSTABLE PRINCESS around the far turn, cut the corner entering the lane, roused for more, responded willingly and drew off. IMPECCABILITY was allowed to settle out of the gate and remained unhurried up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn, launched a rail bid entering the lane and gained second best. CONTRABANDISTA hopped at the start and came away last, rated just off the pace up the backstretch, hustled up three wide late on the far turn, sustained bid through the lane and cleared a share. UNSTABLE PRINCE was forwardly placed in opening stages and got carried out a few paths entering the first turn, remained up close stalking the leader to the far turn, launched a bid for command three furlongs from home, raced in strong contention but could not reach the eventual winner and weakened in the lane. LIBERTY'S HAULER was away in good order and got carried out a few paths entering the first turn, stalked the pace three wide up the backstretch, began to lose some interest mid-way, weakened and never threatened in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLEET OF HOOF sped to the lead at the start and quickly established the early lead, saved ground and held clear around the first turn, set soft fractions on top through early stages, continued clear and remained confidently handled and raced in hand when DEADPIRATEROBERTS loomed a threat near the quarter pole, turned away bid and cut the corner entering the lane, roused for more in upper stretch, responded willingly and drew off to an easy score. DREADPIRATEROBERTS was forwardly placed around the first turn and stalked the leader into the backstretch, edged a bit closer nearing the half mile marker, came under a ride around the far turn, loomed a threat to FLEET OF HOOF near the quarter pole, failed to reach the leader but continued to chase after pulling away winner through the lane and finished clearly second best. ONE LAST CHANT raced off the clear top two leaders up the backstretch, hustled along three wide around the far turn and kept on for a share. PISTOL PACKIN MAN was reserved racing in the back, hustled along three to four wide into the drive and never threatened.
